                                                      <h2 id=3D"what-is-cov=
ariance">What is Covariance?</h2>
<p>In mathematics and <a href=3D"https://corporatefinanceinstitute.com/reso=
urces/data-science/basic-statistics-concepts/">statistics</a>, covariance i=
s a measure of the relationship between two random variables. The metric ev=
aluates how much =E2=80=93 to what extent =E2=80=93 the variables change to=
gether. In other words, it is essentially a measure of the variance between=
 two variables. However, the metric does not assess the dependency between =
variables.</p>
<p><img fetchpriority=3D"high" class=3D"aligncenter wp-image-22843 lazy laz=
y-loading" src=3D"data:image/svg+xml,&lt;svg id=3D&quot;L4&quot; xmlns=3D&q=
uot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot; xmlns:xlink=3D&quot;http://www.w3.org/=
1999/xlink&quot; x=3D&quot;0px&quot; y=3D&quot;0px&quot; viewBox=3D&quot;0 =
0 1024 653&quot; xml:space=3D&quot;preserve&quot;&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;" alt=3D"C=
ovariance - Image of an individual checking financial reports on a tablet" =
width=3D"1024" height=3D"653" decoding=3D"async" data-src=3D"https://cdn.co=
rporatefinanceinstitute.com/assets/covariance8.jpeg"></p>
<p>Unlike the correlation coefficient, covariance is measured in units. The=
 units are computed by multiplying the units of the two variables. The vari=
ance can take any positive or negative values. The values are interpreted a=
s follows:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Positive covariance</strong>: Indicates that two variables tend=
 to move in the same direction.</li>
<li><strong>Negative covariance</strong>: Reveals that two variables tend t=
o move in inverse directions.</li>
</ul>
<p>In <a href=3D"https://corporatefinanceinstitute.com/resources/?topics=3D=
111064">finance</a>, the concept is primarily used in portfolio theory. One=
 of its most common applications in portfolio theory is the <a href=3D"http=
s://corporatefinanceinstitute.com/resources/management/diversification/">di=
versification</a> method, using the covariance between assets in a portfoli=
o. By choosing assets that do not exhibit a high positive covariance with e=
ach other, the unsystematic risk can be partially eliminated.</p>
<p>CFI=E2=80=99s <strong><a href=3D"https://corporatefinanceinstitute.com/c=
ourse/financial-math-corporate-finance/">Math for Corporate Finance Course<=
/a>&nbsp;</strong>explores the financial mathematics concepts required for =
<a href=3D"https://corporatefinanceinstitute.com/resources/financial-modeli=
ng/what-is-financial-modeling/">Financial Modeling.</a></p>
<h3 id=3D"formula-for-covariance">Formula for Covariance</h3>
<p>The covariance formula is similar to the formula for correlation and dea=
ls with the calculation of data points from the average value in a dataset.=
 For example, the covariance between two random variables X and Y can be ca=
lculated using the following formula (for population):</p>
<p><img class=3D"aligncenter wp-image-22813 lazy lazy-loading" src=3D"data:=
image/svg+xml,&lt;svg id=3D&quot;L4&quot; xmlns=3D&quot;http://www.w3.org/2=
000/svg&quot; xmlns:xlink=3D&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink&quot; x=3D&q=
uot;0px&quot; y=3D&quot;0px&quot; viewBox=3D&quot;0 0 330 71&quot; xml:spac=
e=3D&quot;preserve&quot;&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;" alt=3D"Covariance Formula (Popula=
tion)" width=3D"330" height=3D"71" decoding=3D"async" data-src=3D"https://c=
dn.corporatefinanceinstitute.com/assets/covariance1.png"></p>
<p>For a sample covariance, the formula is slightly adjusted:</p>
<p><img class=3D"aligncenter wp-image-22814 lazy lazy-loading" src=3D"data:=
image/svg+xml,&lt;svg id=3D&quot;L4&quot; xmlns=3D&quot;http://www.w3.org/2=
000/svg&quot; xmlns:xlink=3D&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink&quot; x=3D&q=
uot;0px&quot; y=3D&quot;0px&quot; viewBox=3D&quot;0 0 330 66&quot; xml:spac=
e=3D&quot;preserve&quot;&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;" alt=3D"Covariance Formula (Sample=
)" width=3D"330" height=3D"66" decoding=3D"async" data-src=3D"https://cdn.c=
orporatefinanceinstitute.com/assets/covariance2.png"></p>
<p>Where:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>X<sub>i&nbsp;</sub></strong>=E2=80=93 the values of the X-varia=
ble</li>
<li><strong>Y</strong><sub><strong>j</strong>&nbsp;</sub>=E2=80=93 the valu=
es of the Y-variable</li>
<li><b>X=CC=84&nbsp;</b>=E2=80=93 the mean (average) of the X-variable</li>
<li><strong>=C8=B2</strong> =E2=80=93 the mean (average) of the Y-variable<=
/li>
<li><strong>n</strong> =E2=80=93 the number of data points</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"covariance-vs-correlation">Covariance vs. Correlation</h3>
<p>Covariance and correlation both primarily assess the relationship betwee=
n variables. The closest analogy to the relationship between them is the re=
lationship between the variance and <a href=3D"https://corporatefinanceinst=
itute.com/resources/data-science/standard-deviation/">standard deviation</a=
>.</p>
<p><strong>Covariance</strong> measures the total variation of two random v=
ariables from their expected values. Using covariance, we can only gauge th=
e direction of the relationship (whether the variables tend to move in tand=
em or show an inverse relationship). However, it does not indicate the stre=
ngth of the relationship, nor the dependency between the variables.</p>
<p>On the other hand, <strong>correlation</strong> measures the strength of=
 the relationship between variables. Correlation is the scaled measure of c=
ovariance. It is dimensionless. In other words, the correlation coefficient=
 is always a pure value and not measured in any units.</p>
<p>The relationship between the two concepts can be expressed using the for=
mula below:</p>
<p><img loading=3D"lazy" class=3D"aligncenter wp-image-22815 lazy lazy-load=
ing" src=3D"data:image/svg+xml,&lt;svg id=3D&quot;L4&quot; xmlns=3D&quot;ht=
tp://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot; xmlns:xlink=3D&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/x=
link&quot; x=3D&quot;0px&quot; y=3D&quot;0px&quot; viewBox=3D&quot;0 0 230 =
66&quot; xml:space=3D&quot;preserve&quot;&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;" alt=3D"Covarianc=
e vs. Correlation - Formula" width=3D"230" height=3D"66" decoding=3D"async"=
 data-src=3D"https://cdn.corporatefinanceinstitute.com/assets/covariance3.p=
ng"></p>
<p>Where:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>=CF=81(X,Y)</strong> =E2=80=93 the correlation between the vari=
ables X and Y</li>
<li><strong>Cov(X,Y) </strong>=E2=80=93 the covariance between the variable=
s X and Y</li>
<li><strong>=CF=83<sub>X&nbsp;</sub></strong>=E2=80=93 the standard deviati=
on of the X-variable</li>
<li><strong>=CF=83</strong><sub><strong>Y</strong>&nbsp;</sub>=E2=80=93 the=
 standard deviation of the Y-variable</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"example-of-covariance">Example of Covariance</h3>
<p>John is an investor. His portfolio primarily tracks the performance of t=
he <a href=3D"https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/%5EGSPC/" target=3D"_blank" r=
el=3D"noopener">S&amp;P 500</a> and John wants to add the stock of ABC Corp=
. Before adding the stock to his portfolio, he wants to assess the directio=
nal relationship between the stock and the S&amp;P 500.</p>
<p>John does not want to increase the unsystematic risk of his portfolio. T=
hus, he is not interested in owning securities in the portfolio that tend t=
o move in the same direction.</p>
<p>John can calculate the covariance between the stock of ABC Corp. and S&a=
mp;P 500 by following the steps below:</p>
<p style=3D"padding-left: 30px;"><strong>1. Obtain the data.</strong></p>
<p style=3D"padding-left: 30px;">First, John obtains the figures for both A=
BC Corp. stock and the S&amp;P 500. The prices obtained are summarized in t=
he table below:</p>
<p><img loading=3D"lazy" class=3D"aligncenter wp-image-30343 lazy lazy-load=
ing" src=3D"data:image/svg+xml,&lt;svg id=3D&quot;L4&quot; xmlns=3D&quot;ht=
tp://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot; xmlns:xlink=3D&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/x=
link&quot; x=3D&quot;0px&quot; y=3D&quot;0px&quot; viewBox=3D&quot;0 0 400 =
213&quot; xml:space=3D&quot;preserve&quot;&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;" alt=3D"Covarian=
ce Sample Data" width=3D"400" height=3D"213" decoding=3D"async" data-src=3D=
"https://cdn.corporatefinanceinstitute.com/assets/Covariance-Sample-Data.pn=
g"></p>
<p style=3D"padding-left: 30px;"><strong>2. Calculate the mean (average) pr=
ices for each asset.</strong></p>
<p><img loading=3D"lazy" class=3D"aligncenter wp-image-30346 lazy lazy-load=
ing" src=3D"data:image/svg+xml,&lt;svg id=3D&quot;L4&quot; xmlns=3D&quot;ht=
tp://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot; xmlns:xlink=3D&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/x=
link&quot; x=3D&quot;0px&quot; y=3D&quot;0px&quot; viewBox=3D&quot;0 0 700 =
183&quot; xml:space=3D&quot;preserve&quot;&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;" alt=3D"Mean S&a=
mp;P 500 ABC Corp Data" width=3D"700" height=3D"183" decoding=3D"async" dat=
a-src=3D"https://cdn.corporatefinanceinstitute.com/assets/mean-sp-500-abc-c=
orp-data-1024x268.png"></p>
<p style=3D"padding-left: 30px;"><strong>3. For each security, find the dif=
ference between each value and mean price.</strong></p>
<p><img loading=3D"lazy" class=3D"aligncenter wp-image-30345 lazy lazy-load=
ing" src=3D"data:image/svg+xml,&lt;svg id=3D&quot;L4&quot; xmlns=3D&quot;ht=
tp://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot; xmlns:xlink=3D&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/x=
link&quot; x=3D&quot;0px&quot; y=3D&quot;0px&quot; viewBox=3D&quot;0 0 800 =
300&quot; xml:space=3D&quot;preserve&quot;&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;" alt=3D"Covarian=
ce Sample Table" width=3D"800" height=3D"300" decoding=3D"async" data-src=
=3D"https://cdn.corporatefinanceinstitute.com/assets/Covariance-Sample-Tabl=
e-1024x384.png"></p>
<p style=3D"padding-left: 30px;"><strong>4. Multiply the results obtained i=
n the previous step.</strong></p>
<p style=3D"padding-left: 30px;"><strong>5. Using the number calculated in =
step 4, find the covariance.</strong></p>
<p><img loading=3D"lazy" class=3D"aligncenter wp-image-30347 lazy lazy-load=
ing" src=3D"data:image/svg+xml,&lt;svg id=3D&quot;L4&quot; xmlns=3D&quot;ht=
tp://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot; xmlns:xlink=3D&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/x=
link&quot; x=3D&quot;0px&quot; y=3D&quot;0px&quot; viewBox=3D&quot;0 0 700 =
122&quot; xml:space=3D&quot;preserve&quot;&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;" alt=3D"covarian=
ce calculation" width=3D"700" height=3D"122" decoding=3D"async" data-src=3D=
"https://cdn.corporatefinanceinstitute.com/assets/covariance-calculation.pn=
g"></p>
<p>In such a case, the positive covariance indicates that the price of the =
stock and the S&amp;P 500 tend to move in the same direction.</p>
